>> title: Lemon Herb Chicken with Orzo
>> servings: 4
>> prep time: 20 minutes
>> cook time: 30 minutes

1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).

2. In a bowl, whisk together @extra virgin olive oil{0.25%cup}, lemon juice, @garlic{3%cloves}, @oregano{1%tsp}, @thyme{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

3. Place chicken breasts in a baking dish and pour half the herb mixture over them. Let marinate for 15 minutes.

4. Bake chicken for 25-30 minutes until internal temperature reaches 165°F.

5. Meanwhile, cook orzo according to package directions. Drain and return to pot.

6. Add remaining herb mixture to the cooked orzo along with diced @tomatoes{2%large} and @basil{0.25%cup}. Toss well.

7. Steam @green beans{1%lb} until tender-crisp, about 5-6 minutes.

8. Let chicken rest 5 minutes before slicing.

9. Serve sliced chicken over the herbed orzo with @green beans{1%lb} on the side.

-- Category: Mediterranean
-- Cholesterol benefits: Lean chicken breast is low in saturated fat. Olive oil and herbs provide antioxidants and healthy fats. The orzo can be made with whole grain pasta for extra fiber. Fresh herbs add flavor without extra sodium.
